text.tspan: Suicide rate vs. death rate from violence, 2019
Death rates are measured as the number of deaths per 100,000 people in a population. Deaths from violence include
the categories of interpersonal violence, conflict and terrorism, and police conflict and executions.
Source: Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation, Global Burden of Disease (2019)
